fedora 24 will not show the plugged UMTS surf Stick, so you are unable to configure/to use the Mobile Broadband/your UMTS surf stick Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
I´ ve tied . systemclt start Modemmanager systemctl enable Modemmanager
but it dosn´ t work.
Similar problem was in F21 and f22.
How reproducible: everytime
Steps to Reproduce: 1.boot fedora 24 2.plug your UMTS Surfstick on any USB Port
Actual results: The Mobile connecton will not Displayed so you can´ t use your UMTS Surefstick
Expected results:
The mobile connection is displayed an you con use your UMTS Surf stick Additional info:

Hi.
I'm wondering if you could include the log so that we could figure out what's wrong. Please start "journalctl -fl" as root, then plug in the device, capture the output and attach to this bug report.
Also, I'm wondering if you could retest with the updated packages from here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-494a721a73
Thank you, Lubo

Could not depsolve transaction; 1 problem detected: 0. nothing provides ModemManager-glib(x86-64) = 1.6.0-1.fc24 needed by ModemManager-1.6.0-1.fc24.x86_64
by the ModemManager-1.6.0-1.fc24.x86_64.rpm package.
No mobile Brodband working at this time

The Surfstick probably comes with some software already, but that software will conflict or interfere with ModemManager. You probably have to pick one or the other, either ModemManager or the software shipped on the Surfstick.
To update with dependency resolution (which is likely the cause of your update failure) you'd do:
sudo dnf update --enablerepo=updates-testing ModemManager
but to do that you'd need to wait for the Fedora ModemManager update to be pushed to updates-testing. In the mean time you could download all the packages linked from the update, but that might be more trouble than it's worth. The update should be pushed to testing in a day or two.

(In reply to Dan Williams from comment #6) > The Surfstick probably comes with some software already, but that software > will conflict or interfere with ModemManager. You probably have to pick one > or the other, either ModemManager or the software shipped on the Surfstick. > > To update with dependency resolution (which is likely the cause of your > update failure) you'd do: > > sudo dnf update --enablerepo=updates-testing ModemManager
Please, also do
dnf update --enablerepo=updates-testing usb_modeswitch\*
and reconnect your modem. It seems that your modem is not switched from the CD-ROM emulation mode and there were issues fixed in the mode switching tool.
Thank you

The ModemManager update has now been pushed to the testing repo, so you can just do:
dnf update --enablerepo=updates-testing ModemManager usb_modeswitch\*
and do both the MM and usb_modeswitch updates in one command.
